  "why": "The paper (BET) both (1) treats semantic consistency as applicable (single-model testing uses ground-truth labels and assumes mutated inputs should preserve semantics) and (2) enforces strong per-seed perturbation bounds and per-pixel restrictions that prevent cumulative drift across iterations. BET fixes the absolute perturbation magnitude (each perturbed pixel is limited to ±ε relative to the original seed), uses an L∞ constraint (13/255) across experiments, and the mutator logic ensures bytes toggle only between original±ε rather than accumulating changes. These design choices preserve naturalness and semantic similarity to the original seed throughout iterative mutations, satisfying the metric's requirements for High input plausibility.",
